  "scientificVerdict": "The original Maeda deposit does not report a measured Reynolds number or complete atmospheric state; the published CFD convention remains an explicit sensitivity input. The c8, c12, and c16 measured-wing feasibility runs remain non-finite and are not quantitative bird results. A host-plumbing audit found that the stationary-sphere validation had incorrectly copied referenceSpeedLattice into the GPU wall velocity instead of the requested wallVelocityLattice. After correction, the true zero-wall, 0.08-flow sphere fails at step 105 for all three published margins, with zero topology events. The 500-step relaxation response is monotonic: failure moves from step 105 to 454 as tauPlus margin rises, and stability begins between margins 0.00999999 and 0.01249999. At c16 the first negative occurs at step 27, q=10, cell (5,9,12), adjacent to the sphere but pulled from ordinary fluid. The symmetric TRT increment -0.03093607 creates the negative while the antisymmetric increment is stabilizing. A symmetric limiter keeps the corrected c16 case finite and positive through 500 steps. Its global ledger closes population change and attributes the old raw gates to open far-field replacement and sponge relaxation; the limiter contributes only 4.69e-7 of initial mass and boundary load closes to 3.03e-7 relative RMS. The source-aware rerun places the control volume at [4,4,4] through [52,20,20], wholly outside the four-cell sponge, with zero solid surface-crossing links. It retains positive finite populations, closes the global source ledger, and passes the raw force budget: 0.000464 N peak against 0.0005 N and 0.00537% relative RMS. The c16 limiter is therefore accepted for the c8/c12/c16 refinement ladder, but remains excluded from coupled bird replay until resolution robustness is demonstrated."
